FY 2025 Plans:
Specific CPS T&E efforts include:
- Develop the final ZUMWALT-specific shipboard test requirements in coordination with the SSP-lead planning of
the live-fire test event of the CPS Weapon System on DDG 1000.
- Provide ZUMWALT support for shakedown events prior to integration and testing of the CPS Weapon System
on DDG 1000.
- Support execution of the first CPS flight test (SSP-led live-fire test event) from a ZUMWALT Class Destroyer
during JFC-6 with platform and combat system specific subject matter experts, test equipment, and analysis
- Collect data and perform analysis upon JFC-6 completion to support ZUMWALT-specific test objectives
- Start development and refinement of ZUMWALT-specific test objectives/plans and data collection to support
future ZUMWALT Class Destroyer testing.
- Develop plans to conduct ZUMWALT-unique CPS Weapons System testing and procure associated test
equipment and updated weapon system simulators based on changes to the weapon system.

Specific DDG 1000 TEMP efforts include:
- Execute Tomahawk Live Fire test and data analysis and reporting to support Initial Operational Capability (IOC)
declaration
- Develop plans for execution of Follow-on Test and Evaluation (FOT&E) test events, to include Anti-Air Warfare
testing.
- Complete execution of M&S assessment of PRA ASCM and PRA Aircraft KPPs.
- Complete reporting on Live Fire Test and Evaluation (LFT&E) testing, to include the Final Vulnerability
Assessment Report.

Specific DDG 1000 T&E efforts include:
- Execute SM-6 live fire demonstration on DDG 1001 and data analysis and reporting.
