Remarks

D. Acquisition Strategy
The Joint Non-Lethal Weapons (JNLW) project provides commanders the power to dominate the escalation ladder, delivering intermediate force capabilities that bridge
the gap between simple presence and lethal engagement in defense of our national interests. This programs strategy is to pursue the fielding of NLW systems through
modifying commercial-off-the-shelf (COTS) products for near term capabilities and the development of new technology. This program delivers a balanced portfolio
of capabilities, advancing currently fielded NLW systems through a flexible, Lead-Service-driven acquisition process while simultaneously pursuing next-generation
advantages through investment in state-of-the-art technology, experimentation, and advanced simulation.




