C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                  FY 2025     FY 2026       FY 2027
Title: Enterprise Mission Integration and Analysis                                                                                          -       84.134       171.317
Description: Enterprise Mission Integration and Analysis assesses, validates, and in collaboration with USSF Program Executive
Officers (PEOs) and Portfolio Acquisition Executives (PAEs), funds the USSF's ability to close combatant command prioritized
mission threads and kill chains to achieve space superiority and provide space support to the joint force. This effort executes
end-to-end mission thread analysis on operational scenarios needed to deliver mission effects as identified in Combatant
Commanders' Operational Plans using robust System-of-Systems Engineering (SoSE) processes. This includes aligning cross-
program interfaces, system-of-systems tests, multiple program schedules, identifying gaps, and driving integration requirements
with the Chief Strategy and Resourcing Officer (CSRO) for 8 PEO/PAE portfolios' acquisitions to meet warfighter needs.

This synchronizes the USSF's existing, programmed, and objective architectures to provide integrated combat capabilities. It
includes modeling and simulation tools, multi-level security data architecture, and subject matter expertise for analysis, mission
engineering, communication, and collaboration across the space enterprise. This includes rapid response to implement system
resiliency and awareness necessary to operate in the contested space domain. This effort also supports the integration and
modifications of USSF capabilities to realize the DAF Battle Network, enabling space support to the joint fight and increasing
interoperability to achieve sensor-to-shooter effects. It includes the collection and analysis of programmatic data to identify
efficiencies and provide prioritization recommendations to USSF leadership.

SSIO partners with PEOs/PAEs to acquire and integrate capabilities to deliver a fully integrated, resilient, and lethal end-
to-end system-of-systems architecture for multi-domain warfare. In FY2027, this effort expands beyond assessing and
validating warfighter-priority mission threads and kill chains to include budget to directly fund acquisition and integration to
close documented capability gaps. This will be executed by directly funding specific PEO/PAE program increments, system
modifications, and new technology procurements. This direct-funding approach ensures enterprise-level priorities are resourced
appropriately, preventing critical integration tasks from being deferred and guaranteeing that solutions are delivered with the
urgency required to counter peer adversaries.

FY 2026 Plans:
Integrate space command and control (C2) capabilities across USSF PEO portfolios and mission partner organizations to close
kill chains and enable effective and resilient counterspace operations. Develop an end-to-end, system-of-systems test plan to
test the integration of 4+ weapon systems across the USSF needed to execute the Joint Space Operations Plan (JSOP). The

