Surveillance

A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This project develops technologies to ensure spacecraft survivability and to enhance surveillance of the space operating environment. Technology development to
enhance the ability of space assets to operate effectively despite the challenges of the space environment. This includes developing radiation-hardened electronics and
technologies to understand and mitigate impacts of the space environment. The focus is on characterizing and forecasting the battlespace environment for more realistic
space system design, modeling, and simulation, as well as the battlespace environment's effect on space systems' performance. This includes technologies to specify
and forecast the space environment for planning operations, ensure uninterrupted system performance, optimize space-based surveillance operations, and provide
capability to mitigate or exploit the space environment for both offensive and defensive operations.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                      FY 2025        FY 2026      FY 2027
Title: Space Environment Research                                                                                                           22.946         24.141       17.592
Description: Develop techniques, forecasting tools, sensors, and technologies for specifying, monitoring, predicting, and
controlling space environmental conditions hazardous to Department of War (DoW) operational space and radar systems.

FY 2026 Plans:
Continue:
-Executing joint roadmap with the Military Application of the Space Environment (MASE) program at Space Systems Command.
-Developing Over the Horizon Radar propagation specification work and move into more stressing environments, i.e. Equatorial
and High Latitude.
-Collaboration with the United Kingdom, Australia, and Canada, to execute relevant field experiments and develop specification
models with utility for operational systems.
-Supporting and developing technologies aligned to Space Warfighting Analysis Center and Space Systems Command Capability
Collaboration Team tech needs as well as those supporting the Department of the Air Force priorities, e.g. situational awareness
and communication in contested environments; edge sensing and sensemaking; and space environment Common Operating
Pictures.
-Collaboration with Canada on high-latitude ionospheric specification and field experiments.
-Pursuing field experiments and demonstrations related to ionospheric modification.
-Invention and development of space based environmental monitoring sensors.
-Supporting Space Systems Command to optimize the utility of their operational space environment sensor and capabilities in
support of Department of War mission.



