A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This project demonstrates non-traditional waveforms and technologies for resilient communications in contested environments providing anti-jam, low probability of
intercept, and low probability of detection for the dismounted and vehicular user. This project also optimizes technologies not typically applied to the tactical environment,
such as millimeter wave communications and directional networking with coherent combining of radio frequency signals, to maintain networked communications in and
under contested and congested electromagnetic spectrum environments.

Work in this project complements Program Element (PE) 0602146A (Network C3I Technology) / Project AN3 (Non Traditional Waveforms Technology) and Project AO4
(Energy Efficient Devices Technology).

Work in this project is performed by the Command, Control, Computers, Communications, Cyber, Intelligence, Surveillance, and Reconnaissance (C5ISR) Center.

