Description: This effort matures commercial technical effects technology with an emphasis on blue force communications
deconfliction, high fidelity pattern of life generation, and orchestration software. This effort provides the capability to create a radio
frequency (RF) "smoke screen" for the network that will overwhelm adversary electronic support capability resulting in increased
difficulty to find and fix targets based on their RF. This capability has applications at Division and below and the CEMA cell efforts
to create periods of spectrum dominance during the dominate phase of conflict.

Title: Quantum Sensing                                                                                                                             -        1.260               -
Description: This effort demonstrates the use of novel quantum-enhanced spectral receivers capable of wideband sensing of
extremely low power signals at very large standoff distances. This effort matures quantum component technologies for use in very
sensitive receivers. This effort designs and develops tactically relevant quantum sensors, considering form-factor, size, weight,
power, and receiver performance.

FY 2026 Plans:
Will demonstrate ruggedized prototype in a relevant environment, and optimize design based upon performance and soldier
feedback. Will continue to update and refine build process to identify logistically available components to increase availability of
the system. Will interface with standard Army data processors and networks to provide information into a larger DoW network.
