E. Acquisition Strategy
The USNDS Acquisition Strategy is to develop, integrate, field and sustain USNDS satellite sensors and USNDS ground data processing and distribution hardware
and software as well as mission operational and technical program support to sustain the USNDS capability on GPS, DSP, Alternate Host, and SBIRS; funding is sent
by Military Interdepartmental Purchase Request (MIPR) from DoW and DOE to Sandia, Los Alamos National Laboratories and other agencies on existing DOE/NNSA
contracts. The ICADS 7 Acquisition Strategy was approved in September 2021 and the sole source prime contract awarded in June 2022. USNDS ICS funding for
Ground Technology Program System of Systems will continue until UGNT is ready for delivery in Q3 FY 2025. USNDS requirements are defined in the Operational
Requirements Document dated January 21, 2004 and the 2018 GPS IIIF Capabilities Development Document (CDD).




